## Avoid GitGuardian false positives in Lakebase auth tests

Context: GitGuardian flagged ``tests/test_lakebase_auth.py`` (PR #13,
"Generic Database Assignment") because fixture strings mimicked real
Lakebase hostnames (``*.database.*.cloud.databricks.com``) together with
``PGDATABASE`` / ``PGUSER`` assignments.

Changes:

1. tests/test_lakebase_auth.py
   Replaced synthetic ``PGHOST``/read-replica hosts with
   ``*.example.invalid`` names, ``PGDATABASE`` with an obvious test-only
   name, and non-UUID ``PGUSER``/token placeholders so scanners no longer
   match production-like connection material.

Modified files:
- tests/test_lakebase_auth.py

Tests: uv run pytest -q → 1893 passed, 0 failed in 61.29s
